Problem:
class ClimateController {
  private int temperature;
  private boolean airConditioningActive;

  public ClimateController(int initialTemp) {
    temperature = initialTemp;
    airConditioningActive = false;
  }

  public void updateTemperature(int externalTemp) {
    if (externalTemp > 28) {
      airConditioningActive = true;
      temperature -= 3;
    } else if (externalTemp < 23) {
      airConditioningActive = false;
      temperature += 2;
    }
  }

  public int getTemperature() {
    return temperature;
  }

  public boolean isAirConditioningActive() {
    return airConditioningActive;
  }
}",

If the internal temperature is found to be lower than the usual, can we conclude the external temperature rose above 28 degrees?
